>The below term sheet serves as a binding agreement and creates a contract ("Agreement") between Shift4 Payments, LLC. ("SHIFT4") a Nevada limited liability company, with a place of business at 1455 W Sunset Road, Las Vegas, NV 89119 and CardConnect, LLC. ("CardConnect") a Delaware limited liability company with a place of business at 1000 Continental Drive, Suite 300, King of Prussia, PA 19406 as of the date it is fully executed. The parties agree and acknowledge that CardConnect's obligations under this Agreement are dependent on CardConnect receiving written approval from First Data Merchant
>Services ("First Data"). All activities and obligations shall be in line with our existing MPSA. Upon the termination or non-renewal of the MPSA, the parties will negotiate in good faith to enter into a separate mutually beneficial reseller agreement which will
 >encompass the terms of the existing MPSA as well as new products and services. At that point, both parties-will mutually agree to the new terms.

*   [TL] I've updated the language in red above.

>Background: Both SHIFT4 and CardConnect have existing payment gateways. SHIFT4 desires for CardConnect to replace any existing third-party gateways and primarily utilize it [sic] as their preferred provider of gateway services.

>Terms:
>Exclusivity CardConnect will exclusively use SHIFT4 as its preferred provider of payment gateway services.
>*   For properties that are new and have signed their contract as of March 1, 2016.
>*   CardConnect can maintain their existing merchant base that utilizes CardConnect's
>legacy payment gateway ("Legacy Gateway")
>*   CardConnect has the option to convert a merchant using the Legacy Gateway to SHIFT4 at any time.

*   [TL] CardConnect can continue to offer our existing payment gateway (CardPointe) to new merchants, in addition to offering Shift4. There are a few reasons for this that I
    can explain if necessary.

>SHIFT4 shall be the exclusive provider of EMV, tokenization, P2PE and any other new services at CardConnect's sole discretion.
* [TL] No changes here, but I do want to point out that this item does contradict slightly the preferred gateway provider point above. This says Shift4 would be our exclusive provider of any "new" services.

>Term-The initial contract term shall be for 3 years and will renew two additional one (1) year terms, unless either party gives notice to the other, sixty (60) days prior to the then current term.

>Pricing-The parties will be utilizing a revenue share. SHIFT4 will receive revenue share on all interchange and fees that are incurred during this term. The revenue share will be 100%.

[TL] Please clarify. Are you saying Shift4 would retain 100% of the profit generated from these merchants? So, we would not share in any of the profit?

Pg 3.
6. After nearly two years, I had to decide on whether to renew my commitment or proceed with my
original pre-service plan. When leaving high school, I was going to attend the University Of Nevada, Las Vegas to become
a commercial airline pilot, but during my military service, I confirmed that I wanted to be a technology entrepreneur.
I was very proud of my military service, but I had to make what I knew was the right long -term decision for me.
I did not anticipate that my efforts to follow my passion for technology would, in less than four years, lead to
my creating a company that would grow to service more than 200,000 merchants and 330 POS and PMS software
vendors.

7. This growth did not happen with a single good idea, but with unrelenting work that took every moment
of my day, nights and every weekend, for many years, to build. The growth was gradual, but continuous. As I had
learned at a young age, dedication and hard work leads to progress.

Subject: RE: CardConnect - Shift4 Payments Dispute

Jeff,

First, welcome back and I hope your transition back has been easy. My door is always open to you.

Second, I don't know what you mean about a "unilateral" decision. I've been talking to your staff about these
increases for several weeks, if not longer.

My team assures me that they have been keeping your team aware of these changes, I will address that
internally, but that doesn't change the fact that these cost increases are legitimate and allowable under our
agreement. We have already had to pay the networks the increased fees associated with your traffic, and it has
been extremely frustrating to jump through hoops to get reimbursed for costs Shift4 already incurred.

Card brands regularly increase their fees, both in terms of existing fees and new fees, and those costs are
permissible pass-through costs. Please tell me what fees you object to, and I will consider removing them,
but there have not been any changes to "the terms of our agreement" to my knowledge.

Third, I can't just remove fees in 3 days. Any fee change must be made at the beginning of a month or
quarter. I have no problem discussing each fee with you, but at this point the first time those changes could be
made is January 1, 2018.

I understand that your staff hasn't answered you, but that is not my problem. I would never have
committed to an eight-year deal without any ability to account for changes in card brand fees or other third-
party costs, and I just cannot understand why you are so upset about covering the real costs charged for
processing your accounts. In particular, any fees that were incurred after your acquisition closed are fees that
First Data will be collecting already either by means of higher interchange or passing them on to their ISOs or
merchants like you do every day.

I am always willing to find reasonable solutions, but baseless threats will not make this go any faster.

Thank you,

J.D.
